{
  "text": "Pye et al. [CITATION_1] employ four analytical techniques to provide an indication as to the inter-and intra-site variability of the soil at two locations by analysing nine soil/sediment samples taken from a 1 m grid at each site. Indeed, by assessing the results of these four different techniques they seek to provide an indication as to the potential of each form of analysis to discriminate between the samples derived from each of the two sites. These are worthy pursuits and of great interest to geoforensic scientists, however, there are a number of comments and questions that we feel are important to raise.",
  "citation_candidates": [
